 French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Claris","meanings":["Medieval English and French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."]},{"name":"Clarisse","meanings":["Medieval English and French form of the Latin name <i>Claritia</i>. This may have meant ‘fame’ (an abstract derivative of <i>clārus</i> ‘famous’), but as a given name it may have been no more than an arbitrary elaboration of   Clara .  It was borne by a character who features in some versions of the medieval romances of Roland and the other paladins of Charlemagne, and in recent times by the ceramic artist  Clarice Cliff  (  1899–1972 )."]}]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705184,"age":9,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705185,"age":1